IT Budget




The Las Vegas Sands Corporation operates hotels, casinos, and resorts, including the Venetian, the Palazzo, the Sands Expo and Convention Center, and Sands Bethlehem.  The company also operates international casinos including 4 in Macao, and 1 in Singapore.
The Las Vegas Sands Corporation operates hotels, casinos, and resorts, including the Venetian, the Palazzo, the Sands Expo and Convention Center, and Sands Bethlehem.  The company also operates international casinos including 4 in Macao, and 1 in Singapore.

IT Priorities:
•Las Vegas… MoreThe Las Vegas Sands Corporation operates hotels, casinos, and resorts, including the Venetian, the Palazzo, the Sands Expo and Convention Center, and Sands Bethlehem.  The company also operates international casinos including 4 in Macao, and 1 in Singapore.

IT Priorities:
•Las Vegas Sands Corp. is currently focused on improving its cyber security and data loss prevention operations, and is hiring to bolster its information security team.
•The company is in the process of streamlining its vendor selection process by identifying preferred vendors.
•The company is focused on developing its private cloud systems, and has adopted Microsoft Lync and Office 365 systems.
•Beyond technical support for the enterprise's casino systems, the IT team primarily focuses on eCommerce and data analytics systems.

IT Structure:
•Working alongside the IT department, the Marketing and Sales group handles all eCommerce and customer relationship management.

IT Vendors:
•BMC Software provides data center management services for the company.

IT Intelligence Snippets:
2013:
•The company maintains a fully automated data center virtualized with VMware.
•The IT department supports the company's mobile gaming systems, including In-Running, an application that allows customers to place bets before and during sports games.
•Sands' CRM platform is based on Microsoft Dynamics. The platform is used in all of the company's business units both in the United States and internationally.

2010:
•Sands partnered with Cantor Gaming to create pocketcasino, which allows users to continue to play games, or make bets in areas which traditionally are banned from traditional table-based gaming.

2009:
•Sands selected BMC Software to provide data center management services for the company.





