The Venetian® Las Vegas: About Las Vegas Sands Corporation (NYSE: LVS) | The Integrated Resort






The Venetian Las Vegas






Menu





























Las Vegas Sands Corp.
About











LAS VEGAS SANDS CORP.
About Us In the 1990s, Las Vegas Sands™ (NYSE: LVS) created and introduced to the world an entirely new kind of travel destination: the Integrated Resort.  As one of the leading global developers of destination properties, unlike the other hotels on the Las Vegas Strip, we offer an array of high-end amenities and integrated them under one roof to provide the ultimate guest experience.  From sumptuous suites to plush meeting rooms, celebrity status night clubs, intimate lounges, headliner and resident shows, upscale gaming, ultra-relaxing spa services, a wide range of retail shops and award-winning cuisine, we created a self-sustained world of entertainment at each of our exquisite properties in Las Vegas, Bethlehem (Pennsylvania), Singapore and Macau (China).
Our integrated resorts have become premier destinations for travel enthusiasts around the world.  We have raised the bar of excellence in the hospitality industry, providing unparalleled guest service, a luxurious atmosphere and a dynamic resort experience with each and every visit.
The guiding business philosophy of Las Vegas Sands is to see things from our guests' point of view.  All aspects of our resorts have one and only one goal: to make each guest’s time with us as unforgettably enjoyable as possible.  If you stay at any of our resorts, you will soon see how we continually strive to make the experience all about you.
The Venetian and The Palazzo Among our properties in the United States are two luxury resorts on the Las Vegas Strip - The Venetian® and The Palazzo® - where every room key unlocks a suite.  
The Venetian's standard suite is nearly double the size of the average Las Vegas hotel room, prompting it to be featured in the Guinness Book of World Records as the “largest standard hotel room in the world.”  If Guinness still included this category, The Palazzo (which opened in 2007) would surely be included as well, as it is the world’s largest all-suite resort hotel.
In 2014, TripAdvisor named The Venetian the world's most extraordinarily designed hotel.  When combined with Sands® Expo Convention Center, The Venetian and The Palazzo make up the largest LEED certified building on the planet, a testament to our commitment to sustainability.  
The Venetian and The Palazzo offer a variety of cuisines from a collection of award-winning chefs such as Buddy V’s by “The Cake Boss” Buddy Valastro,  Carnevino by Mario Batali, CUT by Wolfgang Puck, Bouchon by Thomas Keller, and Table 10 by Emeril Lagasse.
The expansive Venetian and Palazzo Congress Center features convention and meeting rooms that span 340 distinct venues and more than 2.25 million square feet of flexible space, including the 85,000-square-foot Venetian Ballroom and the newly remodeled Sands Expo. 
Grand Canal Shoppes® at The Venetian and The Palazzo features  more than 160 luxury boutiques, specialty brands and world-class restaurants nestled around a charming and faithful reproduction of Venice’s Grand Canal, complete with cobbled walkways, street side cafes and live entertainment. Signature brands include Nevada’s only Barneys New York, Jimmy Choo, Diane von Furstenberg, Christian Louboutin, Kenneth Cole, Dooney & Bourke, Hervé Léger and Swarovski.
Located in the heart of the Las Vegas Strip, The Venetian features an indoor streetscape complete with gondolas and singing gondoliers, world-class gaming, exquisite restaurants, a wide variety of entertainment such as “John Fogerty – Fortunate Son in Concert,” showroom headlinersHuman Nature, and the female stand-up comedy series LIPSHTICK – The Perfect Shade of Stand Up.
Other unique offerings include the chic dining and nightlife hotspots, TAO and LAVO; the world’s largest Canyon Ranch SpaClub®; and Lagasse’s Stadium, the ultimate sports bar, sports book and restaurant on the Strip.
The Palazzo and The Venetian Las Vegas are the first ever Alliance Resorts in the InterContinental Hotel Group global portfolio.
Our Other Resorts Also in the United States is Sands® Casino Resort Bethlehem, situated on a historic steel mill in beautifully verdant Bethlehem, Pennsylvania.
In Asia, we created and own the iconic Marina Bay Sands® in Singapore.  We also developed - through our majority-owned subsidiary Sands China Ltd. - a collection of leading properties in Macau, including The Venetian® Macao Resort Hotel, Sands® Macao, Four Seasons Hotel Macao, The Plaza Macao, as well as our most recent addition: Sands Cotai Central®, which boasts the world's largest Conrad, Sheraton and Holiday Inn hotels.
In addition to our commitment to tourism, we are involved in numerous philanthropic activities through Sands Cares®, our charitable nonprofit organization. We're also committed to global sustainability through Sands Eco 360°, our company-wide initiative to make our resorts the most eco-friendly in our industry.
 













